coordinatorsRegisterTexts.heading: Coordinator Login
coordinatorsRegisterTexts.contentPart1: The Mable coordinator login is perfect for people supporting two or more individuals. It provides access to the Mable platform, allowing you to build out their teams of independent support workers.
coordinatorsRegisterTexts.contentPart2: Typically, the login is used by Coordinators of Supports, Case Managers, Care Coordinators, Support Advisors and Provider Partners. The login provides access to a dashboard, allowing oversight of all the individuals you assist and the independent supports they are connected with via the Mable platform.

profilePhoto.content2: Your photo is an important element in creating a professional profile and a way to add colour and personality. For clients, being able to recognise you when you arrive for your first support session is also important for safety reasons.
profilePhoto.content4: Refer to the photo guidelines and choose a suitable photo
profilePhoto.content5: Click ‘Update profile photo’ and upload your photo, then click ‘Submit for approval’. Mable reviews all profile photos to ensure they meet our photo guidelines
profilePhoto.content6: Your photo will be updated upon approval, which can take up to 48 hours. If there's a problem, we’ll contact you by email

photoGuidelines.content2: Pick a headshot that represents you as a professional
photoGuidelines.content3: Take the photo in soft, natural light
photoGuidelines.content4: Be the only person in the photo
photoGuidelines.content5: Smiling helps you look kind, friendly and approachable
photoGuidelines.content6: Don’t use a low resolution image
photoGuidelines.content7: Don’t use black and white photos and add filters
photoGuidelines.content8: Make sure no sunglasses, hat or hair covers your face
photoGuidelines.content9: Don’t include objects, pets, children or clients

yourBio.content2: Your bio is your opportunity to tell potential clients a little more about yourself. The information you provide helps them understand why you may be a good match and to decide if they’d like a meet and greet
yourBio.content4: Consider what a client might want to know about you
yourBio.content5: Include your key skills and interests
yourBio.content6: Add a sentence about your values and things you enjoy
yourBio.content9: Refer to the bio guidelines before updating your bio below
yourBio.content10: Click ‘Submit for review’. Mable reviews all bios to ensure they meet our guidelines. This can take up to 48 hours
yourBio.content11: Your bio will update upon approval. If there's a problem, we’ll contact you by email

bioGuidelines.content2: Include your key services or areas of expertise
bioGuidelines.content3: Say how long you’ve been providing support
bioGuidelines.content4: Add a sentence about your values and the things you enjoy
bioGuidelines.content7: Don’t list qualified services, for example nursing, unless you've provided Mable with proof of your qualifications
bioGuidelines.content8: Don’t add any personal information e.g. your phone number
bioGuidelines.content9: Don’t share private details of support services you’ve provided clients

WWCC.content2: To provide services for clients under 18 years old, you must have a current clearance for working with children under the age of 18 in your state
WWCC.content4: We only accept clearances for paid employment and not for volunteer or unpaid work
WWCC.content5: Make sure it’s valid for the state where you’ll be providing support
WWCC.content6: Submitting your Working with Children Check
WWCC.content7: Enter your Working with Children Check number and expiry date below
WWCC.content8: Upload a copy of your Working with Children Check, then click ‘Submit for verification’. We’ll verify your details within 48 hours. If there’s a problem, we’ll contact you by email
WWCC.content9: Your Working with Children Check will show as verified in your profile
WWCC.content10: How to apply for a Working with Children Check
WWCC.content11: The Working with Children Check (WWCC) is a requirement for anyone who works directly with children in each state
WWCC.content12: Go to your state’s website to apply. ACT and TAS only: your Working with Vulnerable People must be 'Employee/Volunteer' class

validate.moreThan1500characters: A wonderful serenity has taken possession of my entire soul, like these sweet mornings of spring which I enjoy with my whole heart. I am alone, and feel the charm of existence in this spot, which was created for the bliss of souls like mine. I am so happy, my dear friend, so absorbed in the exquisite sense of mere tranquil existence, that I neglect my talents. I should be incapable of drawing a single stroke at the present moment; and yet I feel that I never was a greater artist than now. When, while the lovely valley teems with vapour around me, and the meridian sun strikes the upper surface of the impenetrable foliage of my trees, and but a few stray gleams steal into the inner sanctuary, I throw myself down among the tall grass by the trickling stream; and, as I lie close to the earth, a thousand unknown plants are noticed by me: when I hear the buzz of the little world among the stalks, and grow familiar with the countless indescribable forms of the insects and flies, then I feel the presence of the Almighty, who formed us in his own image, and the breath of that universal love which bears and sustains us, as it floats around us in an eternity of bliss; and then, my friend, when darkness overspreads my eyes, and heaven and earth seem to dwell in my soul and absorb its power, like the form of a beloved mistress, then I often think with longing, Oh, would I could describe these conceptions, could impress upon paper all that is living so full and warm within me, that it might
